---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About - Yiannos Demetriou" description="About Yiannos Demetriou, MD/PhD student, builder, and researcher.">
	<section class="section">
		<div class="container about-content">
			<h1 class="section-title">About Me</h1>

			<div class="about-text">
				<p>
					I'm a third-year MD/PhD student (G1, PhD in Computer Science) at Wayne State University. I have a passion for building tools and solving problems at the intersection of science and technology. I like turning ideas into reality, especially ones that others think are impossible.
				</p>
				<p>
					I'm just starting my PhD research, which focuses on leveraging AI for medicine. Right now I'm working on a new model architecture for coronary artery segmentation. Before that, I did undergraduate research in epilepsy neuroscience, working on allele-specific gene editing for SCN8A epilepsy and inhibitory neuron pathology in Dravet syndrome.
				</p>
				<p>
					Outside of the lab and medical school, I started <a href="https://joysdawn.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Joy's Dawn Solutions LLC</a> so I could fund myself exploring my passion for building lots of fun things. Through it I build custom software for research environments, like automated electrophysiology analysis pipelines and AI-powered code auditing systems. I also built <a href="https://guildinit.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GuildInit</a>, a game that turns your GitHub activity into a creature-raising RPG.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="skills-section">
				<h2>What I Work With</h2>
				<div class="skills-grid">
					<div class="skill-group">
						<h3>Languages</h3>
						<div class="skill-tags">
							<span class="tag">Python</span>
							<span class="tag">TypeScript</span>
							<span class="tag">C++</span>
							<span class="tag">JavaScript</span>
							<span class="tag">SQL</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="skill-group">
						<h3>Frontend</h3>
						<div class="skill-tags">
							<span class="tag">React</span>
							<span class="tag">Vite</span>
							<span class="tag">Tailwind CSS</span>
							<span class="tag">Astro</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="skill-group">
						<h3>Backend & Data</h3>
						<div class="skill-tags">
							<span class="tag">Supabase</span>
							<span class="tag">PostgreSQL</span>
							<span class="tag">Node.js</span>
							<span class="tag">Edge Functions</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="skill-group">
						<h3>Research & AI</h3>
						<div class="skill-tags">
							<span class="tag">NumPy / SciPy</span>
							<span class="tag">Statsmodels</span>
							<span class="tag">Claude Code</span>
							<span class="tag">MCP</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="skill-group full-width">
						<h3>Pretty Much Anything</h3>
						<p class="skill-note">With Claude Code's help, I can pick up and ship in any stack. Most of my projects were built in languages and frameworks I'd never touched before starting them. The tools above are what I reach for most, but they're not a ceiling.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	.about-content {
		max-width: 700px;
	}

	.about-text {
		margin-top: 1rem;
	}

	.about-text p {
		color: var(--text-secondary);
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		line-height: 1.75;
		margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
	}

	.skills-section {
		margin-top: 3rem;
	}

	.skills-section h2 {
		font-size: 1.4rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.skills-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr));
		gap: 1.5rem;
	}

	.skill-group h3 {
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--text-muted);
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.05em;
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
	}

	.skill-tags {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 0.4rem;
	}

	.full-width {
		grid-column: 1 / -1;
	}

	.skill-note {
		color: var(--text-secondary);
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		line-height: 1.65;
	}
</style>
